What is the core expertise of scientist working in the organization?Major achievements since inception in terms of a) Product developmentb) Technology developmentc) Patentsd) Paper publishedProject completed (give one paragraph for each project) Ongoing projects (give objectives of each project)Classify the projects based on three major categories:1 Product Driven:Project aimed at developing product(s) that may fulfill one or more of the following criteria:a) Development of completely new product.b) Modification of existing product to suit consumer demandc) Development of product, which is not available in free market e.g. defense related products.2 Technology Driven):Project aimed at developing new technology that may fulfill one or more of the following criteria:a) Cost effectiveb) Greener (eco friendly)c) Efficient in terms of Energy consumption/space utilization/ reducing the process time. Etc.3. Research based projects:Research oriented projects are aimed at generation of new ideas and knowledge that may or may not have direct practical application, but may lead to the development of new area of researches which in turn be used for development  of market based products or will fulfill the demand of society. Example is nanotechnology based projects.Life cycle of the project describes the various stages starting from concept generation.  Student is required to know the detailed process for the following steps:a)   Explain the process involved in conceptualizing the project.b)  Formulation of project with PERT chartc)   Explain the processes involved in writing research  proposal  and identification  of fundingagencies/sponsors.d)  Explain the processes involved in internal evaluation / assessment.e)   Explain the procedure involved in submitting proposal to various funding agencies/industry and defensef)   Identification and process of appointing manpower for the project.g)  Explain the procedure involved in procurement of equipment & consumables h)  Management of working on the projecti)   How progress report is prepared, communicated and assessed. j)   Processes involved in publications and patentk)  Preparation   of  working   manual   (for   product   driven   projects)   or  flow  diagram   (for technology driven projects).l)   Processes involved in technology transfer from Lab to commercial use. m) Preparation and submission of the project completion report.Student will learn how the output of the project is assessed for each type of project mentioned in(item no.5)Category 1 (Product Driven)a) Is the  product  scalable  for  industrial  production?  Explain  the  factors  that  determine  the scalability of the product and identify the bottlenecks.b) How the product competes with existing one in the market?c) Whether patent obtained or applied? Explain the processes involved in obtaining the patent /copywrite / trademark.d) Whether any research paper published.Category 2 (Technology Driven):a) Compare the developed technology with the existing one. b) How does it meet the requirement of the Industry?c) Does it lead to the development of new product or a different pr ocess for existing product?e) Is the technology  patentable?  Whether  patent  obtained  or applied?   Explain the processes involved in technology patent.f)  Whether  the  technology   has  been  transferred   to  any  Industry?   Explain  how  (process involved) the technology is being transferred to the commercial use.g) Whether the project generated research papers?Category 3 (Research based projects):a)   Whether all objectives stated in the projects are fulfilled? If not, state the reasons. b)  What is the new addition in knowledge in the field?c)   Whether this knowledge will lead to the development of new research field?d)  Whether the outcome of project will have any practical applications?e)   How many research papers published or patent obtained?

What is the core expertise of scientist working in the organization?Major achievements since inception in terms of a) Product developmentb) Technology developmentc) Patentsd) Paper publishedProject completed (give one paragraph for each project) Ongoing projects (give objectives of each project)Classify the projects based on three major categories:1 Product Driven:Project aimed at developing product(s) that may fulfill one or more of the following criteria:a) Development of completely new product.b) Modification of existing product to suit consumer demandc) Development of product, which is not available in free market e.g. defense related products.2 Technology Driven):Project aimed at developing new technology that may fulfill one or more of the following criteria:a) Cost effectiveb) Greener (eco friendly)c) Efficient in terms of Energy consumption/space utilization/ reducing the process time. Etc.3. Research based projects:Research oriented projects are aimed at generation of new ideas and knowledge that may or may not have direct practical application, but may lead to the development of new area of researches which in turn be used for development  of market based products or will fulfill the demand of society. Example is nanotechnology based projects.Life cycle of the project describes the various stages starting from concept generation.  Student is required to know the detailed process for the following steps:a)   Explain the process involved in conceptualizing the project.b)  Formulation of project with PERT chartc)   Explain the processes involved in writing research  proposal  and identification  of fundingagencies/sponsors.d)  Explain the processes involved in internal evaluation / assessment.e)   Explain the procedure involved in submitting proposal to various funding agencies/industry and defensef)   Identification and process of appointing manpower for the project.g)  Explain the procedure involved in procurement of equipment & consumables h)  Management of working on the projecti)   How progress report is prepared, communicated and assessed. j)   Processes involved in publications and patentk)  Preparation   of  working   manual   (for   product   driven   projects)   or  flow  diagram   (for technology driven projects).l)   Processes involved in technology transfer from Lab to commercial use. m) Preparation and submission of the project completion report.Student will learn how the output of the project is assessed for each type of project mentioned in(item no.5)Category 1 (Product Driven)a) Is the  product  scalable  for  industrial  production?  Explain  the  factors  that  determine  the scalability of the product and identify the bottlenecks.b) How the product competes with existing one in the market?c) Whether patent obtained or applied? Explain the processes involved in obtaining the patent /copywrite / trademark.d) Whether any research paper published.Category 2 (Technology Driven):a) Compare the developed technology with the existing one. b) How does it meet the requirement of the Industry?c) Does it lead to the development of new product or a different pr ocess for existing product?e) Is the technology  patentable?  Whether  patent  obtained  or applied?   Explain the processes involved in technology patent.f)  Whether  the  technology   has  been  transferred   to  any  Industry?   Explain  how  (process involved) the technology is being transferred to the commercial use.g) Whether the project generated research papers?Category 3 (Research based projects):a)   Whether all objectives stated in the projects are fulfilled? If not, state the reasons. b)  What is the new addition in knowledge in the field?c)   Whether this knowledge will lead to the development of new research field?d)  Whether the outcome of project will have any practical applications?e)   How many research papers published or patent obtained?
